    <div class="CardLabel">February 2026 · 5 min read</div>
    <h1 style="margin:8px 0 4px">How to cut freight costs 18%</h1>
    <p class="CardLabel">Three vendor consolidation moves a beverage shipper made to save $280K/yr.</p>

    <p>BevCo (anonymized customer) was paying 5 different drayage carriers + 2 LTL carriers + 1 reefer specialist. Their finance team thought they had "spread risk." Their ops team knew it was a mess.</p>

    <h2 class="CardTitle">Move 1: Single-source LA-LB drayage</h2>
    <p>Consolidating drayage onto one dedicated carrier with a published rate card cut the per-container cost 14%. It also eliminated the appointment-stacking problem (5 carriers each booking the same 7 AM slot).</p>

    <h2 class="CardTitle">Move 2: Reefer + dry into one carrier</h2>
    <p>BevCo had reefer SKUs and dry SKUs. Different carriers meant different rate cards, double-booked stops, and 2 invoices to reconcile. One carrier with a mixed fleet = single rate card, fewer no-shows.</p>

    <h2 class="CardTitle">Move 3: Cross-dock instead of direct</h2>
    <p>Pull from terminal to our yard, decouple, then deliver. Saves chassis demurrage and lets us batch deliveries. Net: same arrival time at customer, $1.20/case lower freight cost.</p>

    <p><strong>Result:</strong> $280K annual savings, 99.1% on-time vs 91% before, single quarterly invoice.</p>

